::DarkMouse::

She watched as Quickstrike left.  She turned and faced the console of the 
drill.  She smiled to herself.
"Maybe he isn't that bad after all."  She was pleased.  He was actually 
being nice to her.  Then she looked at the drill.  It wasn't dissintagrating 
the rock anymore.  She stopped and climbed down.  She moved infront and 
looked at the hole.  She could see daylight shining through. She ran back to 
the drill and enlarged the hole so that a bot could walk through it. She 
moved the drill back and walked outside.

"Hmm, not bad if I do say so myself."

She then realized that for this to be a secret way out, she would have to 
cover it up.  She went back and looked for Quickstrike.  She would need his 
strength to help lift the hatch for her to weld it to a frame.
